# FinanceFlow USA

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.11-blue)
![PyQt5](https://img.shields.io/badge/PyQt5-GUI-orange)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-green)

FinanceFlow USA is a Python-based economic analytics dashboard built with PyQt5, Pandas, and Matplotlib.  
It visualizes investment growth, project completion, and job creation trends across all 50 U.S. states, providing a clear overview of funding efficiency and development performance.

---

## Features
- Interactive PyQt5 GUI dashboard
- Import and visualize investment data from CSV files
- Store information in a local SQLite database
- Generate ROI (funding per job) analytics
- Display nationwide map using Folium
- Includes database creation and seeding scripts
- (Future) Export reports as CSV or PDF files

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-------------|
| GUI | PyQt5, QtWebEngine |
| Data Analysis | Pandas, NumPy |
| Visualization | Matplotlib, Seaborn, Folium |
| Database | SQLite |
| Reporting | fpdf2 |
| APIs (future) | Census, BEA, FRED |

